===Glyph origin===
{{Han etym}}
{{Han compound|宀|公|ls=psc|c1=s|c2=p}} – to hold; to contain.

容 has also largely supplanted {{och-l|頌}} for the sense of “appearance”.

===Etymology===
; to hold, to contain
: Probably related to {{cog|bo|ལུང||holder}} ({{zh-ref|Schuessler, 2007}}). 
; facial appearance
: Note phonetic and semantic resemblance to {{cog|my|ယောင်|t=appearance, semblance}}, though the discrepancy in initials is problematic ({{zh-ref|Luce, 1981}}). 
; “ronna-”
: {{psm|zh|en|ronna-}}. Coined by the [[w:zh:全国科学技术名词审定委员会|China National Committee for Terminology in Science and Technology]] and the [[w:State Administration for Market Regulation|State Administration for Market Regulation]] on [[w:World Metrology Day|World Metrology Day]] in 2023 (20 May 2023).

